window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>There’s nothing wrong with Ely. He’s young, employed, and, most importantly, he knows what he wants: Energy drink, responsive touchpad, and data connection to play Soul Slate. But when a megacorporation called Utiliterra comes after their technological secrets, he and his friends must react. Will matches wits with Andrei, the omniscient CEO, while Cristal confronts BABL, the colossal communications tower. Meanwhile, Ely just wants to be left alone, but he is inevitably pulled into the epic struggle. Finally, he accepts the frightening reality that his decisions matter. He must choose whether to advance a technology that promises comfort while threatening human sovereignty, or risk devastating consequences of resistance.</p>"; 
